        "id": 2067801,
        "name": "Barry Rothof",
        "username": "Barry_Rothof",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/barry_rothof/{size}/1215_2.png",
        "created_at": "2016-11-30T22:25:50.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p><span alt=\"\" role=\"presentation\" class=\"broken-image\" title=\"This image is broken\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-unlink svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#unlink\"></use></svg></span></p>\n<p><strong>1978 Maison Leroy Auxey-Duresses Les Boutonniers</strong> <em>- France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Beaune, Auxey-Duresses (11/30/2016)</em></p>\n<p>First bottle with \u2013 1 cm of ullage; light brown orange colour, strong sherry-like aromas, total oxidized and undrinkable.</p>\n<p>Second bottle with \u2013 2,5 cm of ullage; A wine with corn, caramel and complex aged yellow fruits on the nose. It exploded in the mouth with great ripe citrus mixed with rich nutty flavours and honeyed lingering acidity. This bottle 1978 Leroy Auxey Duresses was superb.<br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<em>Posted from <a href=\"http://www.cellartracker.com\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
